Rahul M Navneeth.name: Rahul M Navneeth
Rahul M Navneeth.quote: There are dreamers, and there are realists in this world, you think the dreamers would find the dreamers and the realists would find the realists; but more often than not, the opposite is true. See; the dreamers need the realists to stop them from soaring too close to the sun, and the realists; well without the dreamers, they might not ever get off the ground.

T Aswath.name: T Aswath
T Aswath.quote: The idea of Heaven is a world where humans know true happiness without worrying about their future and live in bliss. Cherish the now, and let each moment be a step closer to serenity.

Srivatsav Auswin.name: Srivatsav Auswin
Srivatsav Auswin.quote: For those regarded as warriors, when engaged in combat the vanquishing of thine enemy can be the warrior's only concern. Suppress all human emotion and compassion. Kill whoever stands in thy way, even if that be Lord God, or Buddha himself. This truth lies at the heart of the art of combat.

Naveen Prem.name: Naveen Prem
Naveen Prem.quote: Oh, a tree you shall burn! Burn for the sake of the new Lord! Burn the Erdtree to the ground, and incinerate all that divides and distinguishes! Ahhh, may chaos take the world! May chaos take the world!

Raviprasath KJ.quote: Why don't open source developers need a therapist? Because they always get their issues Merged, Resolved, And closed!

Bharath Sanjeevi.quote: Either she froze time, met and married the man of her dreams, unfroze time and smiled at you, or..., you are a dogface.

Albert Richard.quote: "When you are courting a nice girl an hour seems like a second. When you sit on a red-hot cinder a second seems like an hour. That's relativity." - Einstein

Sriman Vikram.quote: Don't Be Sorry. Be Better To Catch A Fly From The Ass Of Zeus Is Not Worth My Time, Hermes! You can no longer hide behind the skirts of Athena. Boy!

Surya Prakash.name: Surya Prakash
Surya Prakash.quote: If it ain’t broke, it doesn’t have enough features yet.

Nadeem.name: Nadeem
Nadeem.quote: All that is gold does not glitter, Not all those who wander are lost; The old that is strong does not wither, Deep roots are not reached by the frost. From the ashes a fire shall be woken, A light from the shadows shall spring; Renewed shall be blade that was broken,The crownless again shall be king.
